The paper discusses the optimization of collaboration in multi-robot systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of blockchain technology for managing collaboration terms is a novel approach, which could also be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of smart contracts, which is a concept commonly associated with blockchain-based systems and could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
